  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment (NC-7 clean Not-accepted)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors scoped-out with documented rationale. Decision outcome is Not accepted because two assessed factors — Discretization error and Model form — each achieved exactly the required level but the marginal evidence base, when weighed against the HIGH decision consequence, does not satisfy the credibility threshold established by the assessment team. The rejection is grounded in the structured evidence and is not attributable to any procedural deficiency; the package is otherwise complete and clean.",
